      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISTER ANATOLY (4) flew the lids from out wide with an impressive turn of foot, going on to clock 22.85 when a 5.5 lengths winner over 401m at this track last time. Good beginner but will need a little luck from a middle draw. Can measure up again. CREEPING MYLO (7) was out of the placings last time when sixth at this track (23.47) but did record best time of the card when winning four back. Speedy runner who can find the front with a clear break from out wide. Can figure in the finish. JAMAL WICK (1) has been settling off the speed lately, finishing fifth (23.54) last time in a Grade 4/5 at this track. Has a good record at this journey. The form from his last run stacks up well. Expected to feature in the finish. LOCO MISS (8) warrants respect following a recent placing.",
